  {
    "title": "Last year, the Malaysian government had signed the \u2018reciprocal trade\u2019 deal with ...",
    "description": "Last year, the Malaysian government had signed the \u2018reciprocal trade\u2019 deal with the US complete with the \u201cpoison pill\u201d provisions and other coercive clauses. The clauses embedded in the deal threatened to void the agreement if Kuala Lumpur signed rival trade pacts deemed by Washington to jeopardise \u201cessential US interests\u201d or \u201cposes a material threat to US security\u201d and required Malaysia to align with US sanctions and other economic restrictions. The trade deal triggered a backlash in Malaysia, with critics saying it has compromised its sovereignty and long-standing neutrality on foreign policy. The interim government of Bangladesh signed a harsher version of Malaysia\u2019s trade deal with the US just a few days before the election. There is hardly any uproar on that treasonous deal, with the odd critics being questioned about their fitness and qualifications to even criticise such a sanctimonious deal. The opposition too has been engrossed in pointless debate in the parliament when the merit of this deal should be the main focus of all discussions in the ongoing session. Is it our enormous Colonial Stockholm Syndrome that is forbidding us to even talk about this deal? Or is it the presence of Mr Khalilur Rahman, a permanent resident of the US, as the foreign minister that is preventing us from even bringing up this deal in public discourse? Well, Malaysia just showed us how we can get out of this. On the 18th of March, Malaysia announced that its agreement on reciprocal trade with Washington is \u201cnull and void\u201d and no longer applies in the wake of the US Supreme Court striking down President Donald Trump\u2019s \u201creciprocal\u201d tariffs. If Tarique Rahman and his Bangladesh Nationalist Party-BNP-led government truly intend to uphold \u201cBangladesh First\u201d ethos, then it should follow Malaysia\u2019s lead and declare this deal null and void too.",
    "link": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid031KeMXMvc264Er8bpRp1rdCw9MosVK7HJb2vp8SAU3rW4B5WSFQQc77kR3KUfHuQul",
    "guid": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid031KeMXMvc264Er8bpRp1rdCw9MosVK7HJb2vp8SAU3rW4B5WSFQQc77kR3KUfHuQul",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-20T09:40:16.854002+00:00",
